    {
      "id": "48afd09218667fda0725c393e483120c9edf32f3",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2022-10-30 22:25:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review+1\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> Neil/Shaun/James - does this fix make sense?\n\nProbably.  I changes a cryptic error message to a meaningful error telling\nyou that you need a new version of rpm-build.\nThe initial release of SLE-15-SP3 had rpm 4.14.1.  Presumably that has problems.\nThe latest update has 4.14.3 which apparently fixes the problem.\n\nIt isn't clear to me why this BuildRequires has to be specific to suse 15.3.\nWouldn't earlier version of rpm have the same problem on all platforms?\nMaybe this is a suse-specific bug - I cannot find any evidence for that though.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
